<h2 style='margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal;
mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.2.4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Scope
Definition<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'>The
scope of this project includes the development of an e-commerce website called
Fleeky Hub for Fleeky Curtains. The website will feature an order system for
the client's customers, which includes creating an account, paying online or
via cash on delivery. The website will have two main features: one for the
client's customers and the other for the admin/owner side. The admin/owner side
of the website will include analytics and inventory management of the products
and serve as a queue list to identify all the pending products that have been
ordered by customers through the Fleeky Hub website.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal;
mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.2.5.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Project
Scope Statement<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:0in;mso-pagination:widow-orphan;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other;
vertical-align:baseline'><span class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
color:black;background:white'>The project scope statement for the Fleeky Hub
e-commerce website project will detail the projects deliverable and the work
necessary to create these deliverables. The criterion for the product is that
the website is functional and can be used by the clients customers, as it is a
working website to navigate and take orders.</span></span><span class=eop><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;background:white'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";
color:green;mso-ansi-language:EN-PH;mso-fareast-language:EN-PH'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;
text-indent:0in;mso-pagination:widow-orphan;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other;
vertical-align:baseline'><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-PH;mso-fareast-language:EN-PH'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:138.9pt;text-indent:-.75in;mso-list:l381 level4 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.2.5.1.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Product Scope Description<span
style='mso-tab-count:1'> </span><o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:84.9pt'><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>The Fleeky Hub e-commerce website is an
online platform designed for Fleeky Curtains' customers to easily browse and
purchase products through a user-friendly order system. Customers can pay
online or through cash on delivery and view their order history and delivery
status. The website also provides inventory management and sales reports for
the admin/owner. Overall, the website streamlines Fleeky Curtains' business
operations and provides a secure and convenient shopping experience for
customers.</span></span><span class=eop><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
color:black'>&nbsp;</span></span><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.2.6.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Product Acceptance Criteria<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'>Product acceptance
criteria are a set of requirements that a product must meet to be accepted.
They ensure the product meets the needs of users. For the Fleeky Hub e-commerce
website, acceptance criteria will guide development to meet requirements and be
delivered on time and within budget.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>1.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;
mso-themecolor:text1'>The website must be accessible from multiple devices and
browsers and be responsive to different screen sizes.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>2.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;
mso-themecolor:text1'>The website must have a secure payment gateway and be
able to process payments accurately.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>3.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;
mso-themecolor:text1'>The order system must be user-friendly and allow
customers to easily browse products, add items to their cart, and complete their
purchase.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>4.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;
mso-themecolor:text1'>Customers must be able to view their order history,
delivery status, and leave feedback for their purchases.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>5.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;
mso-themecolor:text1'>The website must provide inventory management and sales
reports for the admin/owner to manage the business operations effectively.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;
mso-themecolor:text1'>The website must be tested and verified to ensure it is
free of bugs and errors that may negatively impact the customer experience.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>7.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;
mso-themecolor:text1'>The website must meet all applicable laws and regulations
regarding online sales and data privacy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.25in;mso-add-space:auto;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-list:l261 level1 lfo394;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1'><span

<h2 style='margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.2.15.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:13.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Glossary of Terms<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;mso-list:l388 level1 lfo399'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>Level of Effort: Level of Effort (LOE) is how much
work is required to complete a task.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;mso-list:l388 level1 lfo399'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>WBS Code: A unique identifier assigned to each element
in a Work Breakdown Structure for the purpose of designating the <span
class=GramE>elements</span> hierarchical location within the WBS.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;mso-list:l388 level1 lfo399'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>Work Package: A Work Package is a deliverable or work
component at the lowest level of its WBS branch.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;mso-list:l388 level1 lfo399'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;
mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>WBS Component: A component of a WBS which is located
at any level. It can be a Work Package or a WBS Element as there's no
restriction on what a WBS Component is.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:1.0in;mso-list:l388 level1 lfo399'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt'>WBS Element: A
WBS Element is a single WBS component, and its associated attributes <span
class=GramE>located</span> anywhere within a WBS. A WBS Element can contain
work, or it can contain other WBS Elements or Work Packages.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span class=eop><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></span></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:58.5pt;text-indent:-25.8pt;mso-list:l381 level2 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.3.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span></span><![endif]><span class=eop><span style='font-size:
14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Schedule
Management Plan<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<h2 style='margin-left:98.6pt;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.3.1.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span></span><![endif]><span class=eop><span style='font-size:
14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Introduction<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'>Fleeky
Hub scheduling management plan. Business success requires time management in
today's fast-paced environment. To provide our goods and services on time,
Fleeky Hub effectively manages our timetables.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'>The
schedule management plan describes the <span class=GramE>teams'</span> methods
for operating the company of Fleeky curtains smoothly. The group wants to
maximize production, minimize downtime, and optimize resources. This approach
ensures that the group will address client needs while preserving quality and
efficiency.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'>The
document will be tackling the schedule management approach, schedule control,
schedule changes/thresholds, and scope change. To ensure <span class=GramE>all
of</span> the members of the group <span class=GramE>is</span> on the same
page, we will discuss our internal and customer communication processes. Since
the main goal of the business is to satisfy the customers needs, we are
dedicated to using the finest schedule management strategies to attain this
aim.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span class=eop><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span class=eop><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></span></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:98.6pt;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.3.2.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span></span><![endif]><span class=eop><span style='font-size:
14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Schedule
Management Approach<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'>In
this section of the paper, the team will be discussing what approaches the
group will use in terms of managing the schedule of tasks that were previously
tackled in the Work Breakdown Structure (WBS). The team has decided that <span
class=SpellE>ProjectLibre</span> will be used as our scheduling tool, due to
the nature of the software being open source and user-friendly. <span
class=SpellE>ProjectLibre</span> will be used by the group to create schedules
or timeframes for the group to accomplish <span class=GramE>to schedule</span>
all activities that relate to the project, deadlines, as well as project
milestones.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

following are the milestones for the project schedule</span><span
style='mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;
mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:
Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;color:black'>:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:"MS Mincho";
mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;
mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The figure provided
showcases the team composition, hours worked, roles, and allocated budget for a
project. The total number of hours worked by the team amounts to 8,800 hours,
with Bryan Gel Fabellore, the Full Stack Developer, contributing the highest
with 2,500 hours, while Neil Albert Garcia, the Project Manager, worked the
least with 1,350 hours. The team comprises of Bryan Gel Fabellore, Gabriel Luis
Antonio Perez, Joshua Roxas, Pallas Dale Fontiveros, and Neil Albert Garcia,
each fulfilling their respective roles as a Full Stack Developer, Front End
Developer, UI/UX Developer, Project Leader / Quality Assurance, and Project
Manager. The allocated budget for the project is PHP 1,585,200.00, with Bryan
Gel Fabellore having the highest allocation of PHP 600,000.00, followed by
Pallas Dale Fontiveros with PHP 403,200.00, Gabriel Luis Antonio Perez with PHP
300,000.00, Joshua Roxas with PHP 249,600.00, and Neil Albert Garcia with PHP
32,400.00. This figure provides valuable insights into the team's efforts,
resource distribution, and associated costs for the project.</span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;
mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin:0in;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='color:green'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:58.5pt;text-indent:-25.8pt;mso-list:l381 level2 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.5.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><![endif]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Staffing Management Plan<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal><span class=eop><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:24.0pt'>A strong human resource
management strategy is critical to the success of any project. It acts as a template
for how the project team will be managed and structured, and it assists in ensuring
that the appropriate people with the right qualifications are in the right place
at the right time. Roles and duties, communication protocols, and performance management
measures are all part of the strategy.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:24.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:24.0pt'><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='color:black;background:white'>The main objectives, roles, duties, and
procedures involved in staffing the website development project for Fleeky Hub
are outlined in this staffing management plan. It will outline the project's
many phases as well as the manpower needs needed to successfully complete each
one.</span></span><span class=eop><span style='color:black;background:white'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
style='color:black;background:white'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:24.0pt'>Using this plan, the project manager
and project team can effectively manage the project by ensuring that all team
members understand their roles and responsibilities, that communication is open
and effective, and that performance is monitored and managed in a way that contributes
to the project's overall success.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:24.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:24.0pt'>The following significant
elements will be the emphasis of this workforce management plan:</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:59.3pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:
l151 level1 lfo47'><![if !supportLists]><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]>Tasks
and Responsibilities: It is crucial to specify each team member's tasks and
responsibilities to create responsibility and guarantee efficient coordination.
The plan will specify the precise roles needed for the development of the
Fleeky Curtain website and allocate duties accordingly.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:59.3pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:
l151 level1 lfo47'><![if !supportLists]><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]>Skill
Set Requirements: To hire the best people, it is essential to identify the
skill sets and expertise needed for the various jobs within the team. The exact
skill sets required for web design, web development, content generation, SEO,
and project management will be described in this strategy while taking Fleeky
Curtain's particular needs into account.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:59.3pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:
l151 level1 lfo47'><![if !supportLists]><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>3.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]>Recruitment
Strategy: <span class=normaltextrun><span style='color:black;background:white'>It
takes a strong recruitment strategy to put together competent staff. The
strategy will specify how to find and choose the best individuals for each post
by outlining the recruiting methods, assessment standards, and screening
procedures.</span></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:59.3pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:
l151 level1 lfo47'><![if !supportLists]><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]>Training
and Development: In the ever-changing industry of web development, ongoing
education and professional development are essential. This strategy will
emphasize the value of training and development initiatives to advance team
members' abilities and knowledge and provide high-caliber work.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:59.3pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:
l151 level1 lfo47'><![if !supportLists]><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>5.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]>Collaboration
and Teamwork: Any project's success depends on efficient teamwork and
communication. The strategy will cover the equipment, software, and
communication channels that will be applied to promote streamlined teamwork.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:.5in'><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='color:black;background:white'>The group can guarantee that it assembles
a talented and motivated team capable of providing a visually attractive and
user-friendly website by following a thorough workforce management plan. This
personnel management strategy seeks to give Fleeky Curtains a clear road map
for putting together a capable team of experts who will work together smoothly
to develop an aesthetically pleasing and user-friendly website that is in line
with the company's brand and objectives.</span></span><span class=eop><span
style='color:black;background:white'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:.5in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></i></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:98.6pt;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.5.1.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span></span><![endif]><span class=eop><span style='font-size:
14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Roles and
Responsibilities<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:62.6pt'>An effective human resources
management plan is crucial for the successful completion of any project. It
outlines the roles and responsibilities of all project team members and stakeholders,
ensuring that everyone is aware of their individual contributions and how they fit
into the bigger picture.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:62.6pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:62.6pt'>The plan also defines the level
of authority and decision-making power held by each team member, ensuring that resources
are allocated and utilized effectively. By clearly defining competencies and
skill requirements, the plan ensures that the right people are in the right roles
to achieve project success.</p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:62.6pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-left:62.6pt'><span style='mso-ascii-font-family:
Calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:"MS Mincho";
mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi'>Overall,
the human resources management plan acts as a roadmap for the project team,
guiding them towards successful project execution and delivery. &nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:0in'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>The project organizational design of Fleeky Hub
illustrates the project team and the relationships among the main stakeholders.
Typically, the project sponsor is at the top of the chart, followed by the
project manager who oversees administering the project's resources, scope, and
schedule.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

style='font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:.5in;text-indent:0in'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt'>An internal user of the system, such as the developers
of Fleeky Hub and the staff of Fleeky Curtains, may also partake in user
testing and provide input on the system requirements. External users of the
system (Fleeky Curtains customers) may also provide feedback on the usability
and functionality of the system. The organizational chart clarifies the duties
and responsibilities of each stakeholder, ensuring that everyone is aligned
with the project's objectives and aims.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:58.5pt;text-indent:-25.8pt;mso-list:l381 level2 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.6.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><![endif]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Change Management Plan<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The Fleeky Hub
project must have a strong change management strategy in place for it to be
carried out successfully. Throughout the project lifespan, modifications may
need to be identified, assessed, and implemented. This plan offers a formal
framework for doing just that. This plan may be used to manage changes in an
efficient manner, ensuring that they are timely communicated to all
stakeholders and that they are in line with the project's scope and objectives.</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The change
management strategy comprises a structured procedure for submitting, assessing,
and approving changes. All stakeholders are informed of this procedure in
detail and are urged to make any amendment requests they may have. Following
that, the project team carefully assesses these requests, considering their
possible influence on the project's budget, timeline, and quality. Rejected
modifications are recorded for future reference while approved changes are
performed in a planned and controlled way.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Making
modifications outside of the approved change management procedure can have a
detrimental impact on the project's progress and outcome. Therefore, it is
essential that everyone involved with the project understands and follows the
change management procedure. This adherence will assist in ensuring that the
project stays on course and that any adjustments are beneficial to the
project's success.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>By having a
well-defined change management plan in place, the Fleeky Hub project can
effectively address and accommodate modifications, mitigating potential risks
and maintaining project stability. This approach fosters transparency,
accountability, and effective communication among all stakeholders, ultimately
leading to successful project delivery.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span class=eop><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-pagination:
widow-orphan;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";
mso-font-kerning:1.0pt;mso-ligatures:standardcontextual;mso-bidi-font-style:
italic'>Each member of the Change Control Board brings their expertise and
perspective to the decision-making process. They carefully evaluate proposed
changes based on their impact on the project's scope, schedule, budget, and
overall objectives. Their responsibilities include reviewing change requests,
assessing the potential risks and benefits, and making informed decisions that
align with the project's goals.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-pagination:
widow-orphan;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";
mso-font-kerning:1.0pt;mso-ligatures:standardcontextual;mso-bidi-font-style:
italic'>The Change Control Board operates within the established change
management process, ensuring that changes are thoroughly evaluated, documented,
and communicated to all relevant stakeholders. Their decisions guide the
project team in implementing approved changes and help maintain project
integrity and alignment with the predefined objectives.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-pagination:
widow-orphan;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";
mso-font-kerning:1.0pt;mso-ligatures:standardcontextual;mso-bidi-font-style:
italic'>Regular meetings are scheduled to discuss and deliberate proposed
changes, allowing for open discussions, sharing of insights, and reaching
consensus on the way forward. The Change Control Board ensures that all
decisions are made in a fair, transparent, and objective manner, <span
class=GramE>taking into account</span> the best interests of the project and
its stakeholders.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:8.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-pagination:
widow-orphan;text-autospace:ideograph-numeric ideograph-other'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";
mso-font-kerning:1.0pt;mso-ligatures:standardcontextual;mso-bidi-font-style:
italic'>By having a dedicated Change Control Board, the Fleeky Curtains project
can effectively manage changes, maintain project control, and ensure that
modifications are aligned with the project's goals and objectives. The board
serves as a central authority for change governance, promoting accountability
and decision-making consistency throughout the project lifecycle.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h2 style='margin-left:58.5pt;text-indent:-25.8pt;mso-list:l381 level2 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span

class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Communications Management Plan<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<h2 style='margin-left:98.6pt;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l381 level3 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.7.1.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span></span><![endif]><span class=eop><span style='font-size:
14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;font-weight:normal'>Introduction<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=paragraph style='margin:0in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The Fleeky Curtains project Communication Management
Plan includes the methods and procedures to support successful communication
among all project stakeholders. Clear and timely communication is critical for
effective project implementation because it keeps everyone informed, engaged,
and aligned throughout the project's lifespan.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>This strategy serves as a road map for creating
communication channels, defining roles and duties, and delivering information
in an orderly and consistent manner. By putting this strategy into action, we
hope to enhance collaboration, handle problems quickly, and build a shared
understanding among stakeholders.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The customer, project team, management, end users, and
support staff are all involved in the Fleeky Curtains project. Each stakeholder
is critical to the project's success, and efficient communication among them is
essential for meeting project goals.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>This plan's communication objectives include keeping
stakeholders up to date on project progress, milestones, and timelines,
facilitating collaboration and coordination among project team members, gathering
feedback to address concerns, and providing a platform for sharing project
knowledge and updates.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'> </span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Various communication channels will be used to attain
these goals. Project meetings will be held to discuss progress, resolve
concerns, and plan future activities. Email will be utilized for official
updates and document exchange, whilst collaboration tools and instant messaging
platforms will allow for real-time cooperation and casual contact among team
members. Stakeholder surveys will be undertaken on a regular basis to collect
input, and status reports will be distributed to offer an overview of project
achievements and forthcoming activities. In addition, as a consolidated source
of project information, a dedicated project website or portal will be built.</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>To guarantee successful communication management,
roles and duties are clearly defined. The project manager will oversee managing
communication operations in general, while a communication coordinator will
support and coordinate communication efforts. Team members and stakeholders
will communicate actively, offering updates, comments, and requesting
clarification as needed.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Regular reviews will be done to monitor and assess the
success of the communication strategy, which will include input from stakeholders,
communication logs, and project performance indicators. This will allow us to
make the required modifications and enhancements to the project's communication
methods.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:62.6pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>We intend to establish a collaborative atmosphere,
develop effective communication, and <span class=GramE>assure</span> the
successful implementation of the Fleeky Curtains project by adopting this
Communication Management Plan. We can overcome problems, align stakeholders,
and provide a high-quality product that satisfies the requirements and
expectations of all parties involved by communicating transparently and
consistently.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Fleeky Hub project outlines the communication strategy
and protocols for the project team and stakeholders. The plan defines the
following:</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin:0in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:96.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l325 level1 lfo100;
tab-stops:list .5in;vertical-align:baseline'><![if !supportLists]><span

Calibri'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>A.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>Share project updates:</span></b></span><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'> Keep stakeholders informed about project progress, milestones, and key
deliverables. Regular status reports, progress meetings, and email updates will
be used to communicate project updates.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;

</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>Gather feedback:</span></b></span><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'> Establish channels to collect feedback and suggestions from
stakeholders. Surveys, feedback forms, and open forums will be employed to
ensure stakeholders' voices are heard and incorporated into project
decision-making processes.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:60.0pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:96.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l249 level1 lfo102;
tab-stops:list .5in;vertical-align:baseline'><![if !supportLists]><span

Calibri'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>C.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>Resolve issues:</span></b></span><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'> Provide a platform for stakeholders to raise concerns or issues and
ensure they are addressed promptly. A dedicated issue tracking system and
regular project meetings will facilitate effective issue resolution.</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:60.0pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span

<h2 style='margin-left:138.9pt;text-indent:-.75in;mso-list:l381 level4 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.7.9.1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><![endif]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'>Guideline For Meetings<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:84.9pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Meetings that are effective are critical to the
success of any project or company. They provide a platform for team members and
stakeholders to collaborate, make decisions, and share information. Meetings,
on the other hand, may quickly become unproductive and time-consuming if they
lack adequate structure and procedures. The following principles have been set
to guarantee that meetings at Fleeky Curtains are efficient, focused, and
result in great outcomes. These rules seek to foster a climate that encourages
open communication, active involvement, and sound decision-making. By following
these standards, we may optimize the value of our meetings and promote project
success.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:84.9pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:.1pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
0in;margin-left:84.9pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt'><span style='font-size:13.5pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:84.9pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Below are the meeting guidelines for Fleeky Hub

<h2 style='margin-left:138.9pt;text-indent:-.75in;mso-list:l381 level4 lfo384'><![if !supportLists]><span

font-weight:normal'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'>6.7.9.2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><![endif]><span
class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'>Communication Standards<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:84.9pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The best communication standards for the Fleeky Hub
project may include the following:</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Clear and Concise Communication: All
communication within Fleeky Curtains should be clear, concise, and easily
understandable. Use plain language and avoid technical jargon or complex
terminology that may cause confusion.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Respectful and Professional Tone: Maintain a
respectful and professional tone in all written and verbal communication. Treat
others with courtesy and avoid any form of disrespectful or offensive
language.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Timely Responses: Respond to messages, emails,
and inquiries in a timely manner. Aim to acknowledge and reply to communication
within 24 hours, unless otherwise specified.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Active Listening: Practice active listening
during meetings and conversations. Pay attention to the speaker, ask clarifying
questions when needed, and avoid interrupting others.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Use of Proper Communication Channels: Select the
appropriate communication channel for the message being conveyed. Use email for
formal communication, instant messaging for quick questions or updates, and
face-to-face meetings for in-depth discussions or important decisions.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Documentation: Maintain accurate and up-to-date
documentation of all important communication, decisions, and actions taken
during meetings. This includes meeting minutes, action items, and follow-up
tasks.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Confidentiality and Data Protection: Respect the
confidentiality of sensitive information and adhere to data protection
regulations. Only share confidential information with authorized individuals
and ensure that digital communication channels are secure.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Collaboration and Teamwork: Foster a
collaborative environment by encouraging open communication, idea sharing, and
constructive feedback. Value different perspectives and encourage all team
members to actively participate in discussions.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Regular Updates: Provide regular updates on
project progress, milestones, and potential issues to all relevant stakeholders.
Keep everyone informed about any changes or updates that may impact the
project's timeline or scope.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoListParagraph style='margin-left:102.9pt;mso-list:l339 level1 lfo402'><![if !supportLists]><span
style='font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:
Symbol'><span style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Feedback and Continuous Improvement: Encourage
feedback from team members and stakeholders to improve communication processes
and address any issues or challenges. Actively seek suggestions for enhancing
communication effectiveness and implement necessary improvements.&nbsp;</p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:84.9pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:84.9pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>By following these communication standards, Fleeky
Curtains can promote effective communication, enhance collaboration, and ensure
that information flows smoothly throughout the organization.</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

class=eop><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;mso-themecolor:text2;
font-weight:normal'>Communication Escalation Process<o:p></o:p></span></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal><span class=eop><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;color:#1F497D;
mso-themecolor:text2'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Effective communication is crucial for the success of
Fleeky Curtains. However, there may be situations where communication
breakdowns or conflicts arise. To address such issues promptly and ensure that
communication flows smoothly, the following communication escalation process is
established:</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:59.1pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:12.9pt;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><b><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Informal Resolution:</span></b></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span

</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>Step 1: Direct Communication</span></b></span><span class=normaltextrun><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'> - If there is a communication issue or conflict, individuals involved
should first attempt to resolve it through direct communication. They should
discuss the matter openly, actively listen to each other's perspectives, and
work towards finding a mutually agreeable solution.</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span

style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'> - If the issue remains unresolved, the parties involved can seek
assistance from a neutral team member or a designated mediator. The mediator
will facilitate a discussion to help the individuals reach a resolution and
restore effective communication.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span

EN-US'>Visual tools will be used to track the quality control measurements in
real-time so that all team members can readily access and comprehend the data.
It draws attention to patterns and problem areas so that the team can act fast
and make the necessary adjustments.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>The quality control metrics will be reviewed, and the method will be
adjusted as necessary during routine team reviews such as sprint reviews and
retrospectives. Together, the group will pinpoint potential improvement areas
and put any found problems into practice.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

lang=EN-PH style='font-size:13.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:41.25pt;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>In conclusion, the Fleeky Hub project will use Agile and Scrum
approaches to implement a collaborative and dynamic quality control strategy.
To make sure the product satisfies the standards and needs, the team will
regularly assess the product's quality and make the required improvements. On a
common platform, all quality control measurements will be collected and tracked
in real-time. The team will collaborate to address any problems and implement
any necessary improvements.</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

style='color:#2E5395'>Introduction<o:p></o:p></span></h1>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Fleeky
Hub aims to provide a system called Fleeky Curtains.</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>The
risk management plan encompasses the roles and responsibilities of the project
team, the risk assessment plan, and an outline of the risk management process.
It will also detail the procedures for monitoring and managing risks, as well
as the tactics for responding to risks. The plan's efficacy will be evaluated
based on the prompt identification and resolution of threats.</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>The
following are information that are considered when developing a Risk Management
Plan for the project, Fleeky Hub:</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l48 level1 lfo183;
tab-stops:list .5in;vertical-align:baseline'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Identifying Risk:</span></b></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>
Fleeky Hub development, implementation, and operation project group ought to be
aware of any potential dangers. Risks may appear from <span class=GramE>a
number of</span> different places, including&#8239;technical problems, legal
requirements, cybersecurity, and human factors. Risks should be identified and
then evaluated for both chance of occurrence and potential effects on the
project.</span></span><span class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l198 level1 lfo184;
tab-stops:list .5in;vertical-align:baseline'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Risk Monitoring:</span></b></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>
Risk management is an ongoing activity that needs regular observation and
evaluation. To guarantee that risk management procedures are still effective,
risks are updated, and new risks are discovered, the project team should
establish a frequent review process. All stakeholders should be informed of any
changes during the review process, which should be open and transparent.</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l198 level1 lfo184;
tab-stops:list .5in;vertical-align:baseline'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Contingency Plans:</span></b></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>
The project team needs to create backup plans for major risks that could have a
big impact on the project's success. Plans for alternatives ought to specify
the actions needed to lessen the risk's effects and keep the project moving
forward. As the project develops and new risks are discovered, these strategies
should be periodically reviewed and modified.&#8239;</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l198 level1 lfo184;
tab-stops:list .5in;vertical-align:baseline'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol'><span
style='mso-list:Ignore'><span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Risk Mitigation Tactics:</span></b></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>
The project team should create a plan for minimizing or avoiding the risks
after having identified and assessed the risks. Prioritizing mitigation tactics
should be done in accordance with how well they reduce risk and how easily they
can be implemented in terms of both time and money. Contingency planning,
redundancy, risk transfer through insurance, and the creation of fallback
processes are some possible strategies.</span></span><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span class=eop><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>The
Fleeky Hub project team will guarantee the efficient execution of the project,
meeting all objectives and mitigating potential risks by incorporating
additional considerations into a risk management plan.</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</span></span></span><![endif]><span class=normaltextrun><b><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Risk Identification and Assessment:</span></b></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>
Through brainstorming sessions, studies of prior project experiences, and
evaluation of the project's requirements and scope, the project team will
identify project-related threats. The risks will be listed in a risk register
together with details about their likelihood of happening, potential effects,
and description. The identified risks will be assessed in terms of their
likelihood of occurring and their effect on the project. The project team will
rank each risk according to severity using the risk matrix. Risks with a high
level of severity will be prioritized for either mitigation or contingency
planning.&#8239;</span></span><span class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span

style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>Risk Monitoring:</span></b></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>
Risks will be continuously monitored during the project. To ensure that risks
are being properly managed, the project team will frequently review the risk
register. As further threats are found and added to the risk register
throughout the project, the risk assessment process will be repeated.</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:

risks that cannot be minimized.</span></span><span class=normaltextrun><span

style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Calibri Light",sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:#2F5496'>&nbsp;</span><span

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>The
Fleeky Hub Agile Risk Management Plan offers a framework for actively tracking
risks throughout the project. To do this, it is crucial to closely document the
process, including defining the circumstances that might set off risks, and to
regularly monitor risks <span class=GramE>during the course of</span> the
project.</span></span><span class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;vertical-align:baseline'><span lang=EN-PH
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>The
high-scoring risks will be incorporated into the project schedule, and the risk
manager will be given responsibility for their monitoring. This will make it
easier for the project manager to decide when hazards need to be closely
monitored and when the risk manager should provide project team meetings with
updates. The risk manager will <span class=GramE>be in charge of</span>
monitoring the risk-triggering circumstances. The project manager will also
make sure that the project team is informed of the risks that have been
identified and their potential effects on the project. Any new risks or
modifications to existing risks should be reported to the risk management by
the project team so that they can be evaluated and given the appropriate level
of priority.</span></span><span class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span
class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span
lang=EN-PH style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=paragraph style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in;vertical-align:baseline'><span
class=normaltextrun><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif'>The
agile risk management methodology, which emphasizes flexibility and constant
improvement, will be used by the project team. To guarantee that the project's
goals and quality standards are met, the effectiveness of the risk management
plan will be periodically evaluated and changed as necessary.</span></span><span
class=normaltextrun><span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:
EN-US'>&#8239;</span></span><span class=eop><span lang=EN-PH style='font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif'>&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=EN-PH style='font-size:
9.0pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

color:#2F5496;mso-ansi-language:EN-PH'>6.9.7 Risk Mitigation and Avoidance</span><span
style='font-size:13.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Calibri Light",sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:#2F5496'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
